article.headline: Old Dominion 86, UNC Wilmington 70
article.story: WILMINGTON, N.C. (AP) -- Brandon Johnson scored 27 points to lead three players in double-digit scoring and lift Old Dominion past UNC Wilmington 86-70 on Saturday. Arnaud Dahi scored 20 points and Valdas Vasylius added 15 for the Monarchs (14-7, 7-3 Colonial Athletic Association), who shot 76.5 percent (26-for-34) from the foul line. Montez Downey came off the bench to score 21 points to lead the Seahawks (4-15, 1-9), who've lost eight straight to Old Dominion. Todd Hendley had 11 rebounds. The Seahawks led 35-31 at the half. Trailing 59-53 midway through the second half, the Monarchs went on a stifling 25-1 spurt to secure the win.
